                />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="INGREDIENTS:\n\n
•Rajma/Kidney beans - 1 cup\n
•Chilli powder - 3/4 tsp\n
•Turmeric powder - 1/4 tsp\n
•Garam masala - 1 tsp\n
•Coriander powder - 1 tsp\n
•Salt as required\n\n
For Grinding : \n
•Ripe juicy tomatoes - 3 (big) \n
•Green chilli -1 deseeded\n
•Ginger -1 inch piece\n\n
For the seasoning : \n
•Oil -2 tbsp\n
•Cumin seeds -1/2 tsp\n
•Asafoetida/hing - a pinch\n\n
Preparation : \n
•Wash rajma and soak it for 6- 8 hours. Pressure cook rajma with a little salt until soft. \n
•Grind tomatoes, green chilli and ginger to a fine paste and keep it ready. \n\n
METHOD : \n
1.Heat oil in a pan, add the ingredients mentined under seasoning.When cumin seeds/jeera sizzles, add the ground paste, turmeric powder, chilli powder, garam masala and coriander powder. Cook until oil separates. \n
2.Then add the cooked rajma along with needed water (use the water in which rajma was cooked), needed salt and cook for a few minutes on low flame. \n
3.Garnish with coriander leaves. This goes well with hot rice, phulkas and chapati. \n



